{
  "text": "The region r 1 < r < r 2 is termed the \"unswollen\" region. Here, the behavior of the polymer is ideal even over distances longer than the blob radius ξ(r). The polymer is solvated, and the volume it occupies is influenced by the solvent quality through the excluded volume parameter ν ̅ , [CITATION_1] a measure of the interaction volume per monomer. The \"swollen\" region starts at distance r 2 given by",
